                    <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
                    <p>Last updated: January 2, 2026</p>
                    
                    <p>At Arshit Traders, we value our customers and want to ensure you are satisfied with your purchase. If you are not entirely happy with your order, we're here to help.</p>

                    <h2>1. Eligibility for Refunds</h2>
                    <p>To be eligible for a refund, please ensure that:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>The product was purchased in the last 7 days.</li>
                        <li>The product is in its original packaging.</li>
                        <li>The product isn't used or damaged.</li>
                        <li>You have the receipt or proof of purchase.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>2. Non-Refundable Items</h2>
                    <p>The following items are not eligible for refunds:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Custom or personalized orders.</li>
                        <li>Perishable goods.</li>
                        <li>Digital downloads or software.</li>
                        <li>Items on clearance or final sale.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>3. Return Process</h2>
                    <p>To initiate a return, please contact our support team at support@arshittraders.com with your order number and details about the item you wish to return. We will provide you with instructions on where to send your package.</p>

                    <h2>4. Refund Method</h2>
                    <p>Once we receive and inspect your returned item, we will notify you of the approval or rejection of your refund. If approved, your refund will be processed, and a credit will automatically be applied to your original method of payment within 7-10 business days.</p>

                    <h2>5. Shipping Costs</h2>
                    <p>Shipping costs are non-refundable. If you receive a refund, the cost of return shipping will be deducted from your refund unless the return is due to our error (e.g., defective or incorrect item).</p>
